HEADWORD: Glyphography
<hw>Gly*phog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ to
engrave + <ets>-graphy</ets>.]</ety> <def>A process similar to etching,
in which, by means of voltaic electricity, a raised copy of a drawing is
made, so that it can be used to print from.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

